msgid "Start QGIS, select |mActionOptions| :guilabel:`Project Properties` from the :guilabel:`Settings` (KDE, Windows) or :guilabel:`File` (Gnome, OSX) menu and click on the :guilabel:`Projection` tab. As an alternative you can also click on the |mIconProjectionEnabled| :sup:`projector` icon in the lower right-hand corner of the statusbar."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:34
# 4fb0cbc5c4c54898910c96460f1c108e
msgid "Click on the |checkbox| `Enable on the fly projection` checkbox and select a projected coordinate system of your choice (see also :ref:`label_projections`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:36
# 6faab6a8ff0148559d0e0fba551e88c4
msgid "Load the coordinate capture plugin in the Plugin Manager (see :ref:`load_core_plugin`) and ensure that the dialog is visible by going to :menuselection:`View --> Panels` and ensuring that |checkbox| `Coordinate Capture` is enabled. The coordinate capture dialog appears as shown in Figure figure_coordinate_capture_1_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:41
# c078013cc26846aca42e5dc6a6a32676
msgid "Click on the |geographic| :sup:`Click to the select the CRS to use for coordinate display` icon and select a different CRS from the one you selected above."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/user_manual/plugins/plugins_coordinate_capture.rst:43
# 6b914164124f4400a4cfd7cc69f29efc
msgid "To start capturing coordinates, click on **[Start capture]**. You can now click anywhere on the map canvas and the plugin will show the coordinates for both of your selected CRS."
msgstr ""

